WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:11.886 --> 00:00:15.515 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO grunts]

00:00:17.767 --> 00:00:20.687 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Wait, where am I?

00:00:23.898 --> 00:00:25.108 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Uh?

00:00:33.033 --> 00:00:35.076 position:50% align:center
[yelps]

00:00:38.705 --> 00:00:39.914 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
That's a straw house.

00:00:39.998 --> 00:00:43.084 position:50% align:center
And I'm... Almost as if...

00:00:43.168 --> 00:00:44.627 position:50% align:center
Yeah, that's right!

00:00:44.711 --> 00:00:47.589 position:50% align:center
You're all mine now, you juicy
little pudge of a piggy!

00:00:47.672 --> 00:00:52.677 position:50% align:center
--[SHIDO yells]
--[WOLF growls, grunts]

00:00:56.431 --> 00:01:01.436 position:50% align:center
♪

00:02:35.321 --> 00:02:37.699 position:50% align:center
[WOLF grunts]

00:02:40.910 --> 00:02:43.121 position:50% align:center
Jeez, that was really close.

00:02:43.204 --> 00:02:44.497 position:50% align:center
[YOSHINO]
Shido?

00:02:44.581 --> 00:02:45.790 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps]

00:02:45.874 --> 00:02:50.587 position:50% align:center
[YOSHINO] Oh, Shido,
you're here. I'm glad.

00:02:50.670 --> 00:02:53.173 position:50% align:center
Yoshino? What's that outfit?

00:02:53.256 --> 00:02:54.674 position:50% align:center
I have no clue.

00:02:54.758 --> 00:02:57.469 position:50% align:center
I was already wearing
it when I got here.

00:02:57.552 --> 00:03:01.222 position:50% align:center
I was also told to bring this to
Grandma's house for some reason.

00:03:01.306 --> 00:03:04.601 position:50% align:center
It's bizarre. We figured out
quickly that spirit power

00:03:04.684 --> 00:03:06.186 position:50% align:center
and Angels don't work here,

00:03:06.269 --> 00:03:08.855 position:50% align:center
so we didn't have much choice
but to just go with the flow.

00:03:08.938 --> 00:03:10.857 position:50% align:center
Well, it's pretty obvious
that I'm one of the

00:03:10.940 --> 00:03:14.986 position:50% align:center
Three Little Pigs, so now,
what I'm thinking...

00:03:15.070 --> 00:03:17.655 position:50% align:center
Hold on. This is Grandma's?

00:03:17.739 --> 00:03:19.991 position:50% align:center
In Little Red Riding Hood?

00:03:20.075 --> 00:03:25.497 position:50% align:center
[WOLF laughs] What a good little
girl you turned out to be.

00:03:25.580 --> 00:03:26.748 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO, YOSHINO gasp]

00:03:26.831 --> 00:03:28.208 position:50% align:center
[WOLF] Not only did you
come straight here when

00:03:28.291 --> 00:03:29.668 position:50% align:center
you were summoned,
but you thought to bring

00:03:29.751 --> 00:03:32.921 position:50% align:center
a tasty little piggy along
with you, too! Yum!

00:03:33.004 --> 00:03:35.298 position:50% align:center
[YOSHINON] Looks like
Grandma's gone beast mode!

00:03:35.382 --> 00:03:36.383 position:50% align:center
Hang onto your butts!

00:03:36.466 --> 00:03:39.177 position:50% align:center
'Cause I'm gonna
gobble you up now!

00:03:39.803 --> 00:03:41.304 position:50% align:center
[groans]

00:03:46.768 --> 00:03:48.478 position:50% align:center
[NIA]
Hm!

00:03:48.561 --> 00:03:50.814 position:50% align:center
You guys okay? Shido?

00:03:50.897 --> 00:03:52.982 position:50% align:center
We're great. Thanks.

00:03:53.066 --> 00:03:54.609 position:50% align:center
[WOLF growls]

00:03:54.693 --> 00:03:57.445 position:50% align:center
Tohka! Better give
him a millet dumpling.

00:03:57.529 --> 00:03:59.364 position:50% align:center
From your belt! Hurry, Do it!

00:03:59.447 --> 00:04:01.533 position:50% align:center
Huh? One of these?

00:04:10.083 --> 00:04:12.335 position:50% align:center
Oh my gosh. I'm so very sorry!

00:04:12.419 --> 00:04:15.880 position:50% align:center
I get like that when I'm hangry.
it's the worst, you know?

00:04:15.964 --> 00:04:18.133 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Uh, sure.

00:04:18.216 --> 00:04:20.510 position:50% align:center
That's Momotaro's millet
dumplings for you!

00:04:20.593 --> 00:04:22.137 position:50% align:center
They're incredible, aren't they?

00:04:22.220 --> 00:04:25.265 position:50% align:center
For real, who knew
dumplings could do that?

00:04:25.348 --> 00:04:28.101 position:50% align:center
Nia, what the
heck is going on?

00:04:28.184 --> 00:04:31.104 position:50% align:center
Like, were we swallowed
by Beelzebub or something?

00:04:31.187 --> 00:04:32.355 position:50% align:center
[NIA]
Not quite.

00:04:32.439 --> 00:04:34.024 position:50% align:center
It'd be more accurate
to say we're in a world

00:04:34.107 --> 00:04:36.359 position:50% align:center
that was created by Beelzebub.

00:04:36.443 --> 00:04:38.361 position:50% align:center
And you? Which are you?

00:04:38.445 --> 00:04:42.115 position:50% align:center
You mean which story?
I'm Fatima from Silver Bullet.

00:04:42.198 --> 00:04:44.534 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO] C'mon, that's your
own frickin' manga.

00:04:44.617 --> 00:04:47.370 position:50% align:center
Got any clue how we can
get back to our world?

00:04:47.454 --> 00:04:49.998 position:50% align:center
Well, Westcott won't be
letting us out any time soon,

00:04:50.081 --> 00:04:51.583 position:50% align:center
that's for sure.

00:04:51.666 --> 00:04:54.753 position:50% align:center
Which means, our first priority
has to be finding someone who

00:04:54.836 --> 00:04:58.131 position:50% align:center
has the kind of power it would
take to break us out of here.

00:04:58.214 --> 00:05:00.008 position:50% align:center
You think we're just
gonna conveniently find

00:05:00.091 --> 00:05:01.259 position:50% align:center
someone like that?

00:05:01.343 --> 00:05:03.928 position:50% align:center
No idea, but we're
about to find out.

00:05:04.012 --> 00:05:05.555 position:50% align:center
I assume the others
are wandering around

00:05:05.638 --> 00:05:07.557 position:50% align:center
somewhere in this world, too.

00:05:15.106 --> 00:05:20.945 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA, YUZUR pant]

00:05:21.029 --> 00:05:23.365 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Kotori! Hey, are you all right?

00:05:23.448 --> 00:05:26.159 position:50% align:center
[YUZURU] Concern.
She won't seem to wake up.

00:05:26.242 --> 00:05:28.661 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Hm. Well, in that case.

00:05:28.745 --> 00:05:31.164 position:50% align:center
Oh! Shido! Come over here!

00:05:31.247 --> 00:05:32.207 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:05:32.290 --> 00:05:34.459 position:50% align:center
[YUZURU]
Request. Kotori's in danger.

00:05:34.542 --> 00:05:37.212 position:50% align:center
She needs cardiac massage,
immediately.

00:05:41.424 --> 00:05:43.468 position:50% align:center
Hey! What's the big idea?

00:05:46.638 --> 00:05:49.432 position:50% align:center
Look at that!
We sure fooled you, Kotori!

00:05:49.516 --> 00:05:52.143 position:50% align:center
Agreed. I had a hypothesis.

00:05:52.227 --> 00:05:54.270 position:50% align:center
I thought Shido's name might
wake you successfully,

00:05:54.354 --> 00:05:55.897 position:50% align:center
by the sheer power of true love.

00:05:55.980 --> 00:05:57.190 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI grunts]

00:06:00.694 --> 00:06:02.904 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Huh? What this?

00:06:02.987 --> 00:06:05.448 position:50% align:center
I guess I'm the
Little Match Girl.

00:06:05.532 --> 00:06:09.119 position:50% align:center
I can only assume this must
be Westcott's doing, then.

00:06:13.748 --> 00:06:15.333 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:06:15.417 --> 00:06:18.294 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] Is this really just
a vision? It's so real!

00:06:18.378 --> 00:06:22.674 position:50% align:center
[YUZURU]
Wonder! Even Shido is in it!

00:06:22.757 --> 00:06:24.175 position:50% align:center
Lovely.

00:06:24.259 --> 00:06:26.219 position:50% align:center
It would appear that Kotori's
special feelings for Shido

00:06:26.302 --> 00:06:27.679 position:50% align:center
have made their way
into her dreams.

00:06:27.762 --> 00:06:28.805 position:50% align:center
But that doesn't make any sense,

00:06:28.888 --> 00:06:30.890 position:50% align:center
it's supposed to be
her dead grandma!

00:06:30.974 --> 00:06:33.351 position:50% align:center
Anyway, what's your story, huh?

00:06:34.853 --> 00:06:35.979 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
What's this?

00:06:36.062 --> 00:06:37.731 position:50% align:center
It began in a strange way.

00:06:37.814 --> 00:06:41.151 position:50% align:center
We found ourselves in
a forest, and after a bit,

00:06:41.234 --> 00:06:44.029 position:50% align:center
we came upon the cutest
little candy house.

00:06:45.822 --> 00:06:47.323 position:50% align:center
[YUZURU]
Explanation.

00:06:47.407 --> 00:06:49.951 position:50% align:center
We'd gotten quite hungry, so we
decided to snack on the walls

00:06:50.035 --> 00:06:51.870 position:50% align:center
and roof to fill our bellies.

00:06:51.953 --> 00:06:55.040 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI] A-ha. You're Hansel
and Gretel, huh?

00:06:55.123 --> 00:06:57.792 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] This creepy old hag
did actually try talking to us

00:06:57.876 --> 00:07:01.129 position:50% align:center
at one point, but we just
ignored her and ran away.

00:07:01.212 --> 00:07:03.381 position:50% align:center
[YUZURU] Concur.
She chased us with a speed

00:07:03.465 --> 00:07:05.759 position:50% align:center
that was both surprising
and terrifying.

00:07:05.842 --> 00:07:07.093 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
She tried.

00:07:07.177 --> 00:07:09.971 position:50% align:center
But let's be real, nobody can
keep pace with us!

00:07:10.055 --> 00:07:11.348 position:50% align:center
[YUZURU]
Truth.

00:07:11.431 --> 00:07:13.558 position:50% align:center
Kaguya had tears in her eyes
and may have, in fact,

00:07:13.641 --> 00:07:15.226 position:50% align:center
peed on herself a little bit.

00:07:15.310 --> 00:07:17.979 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA gasps]
I did not pee myself!

00:07:25.737 --> 00:07:27.906 position:50% align:center
Well, We've gotta get
it together, find the others,

00:07:27.989 --> 00:07:30.241 position:50% align:center
and get back to
our world ASAP.

00:07:30.325 --> 00:07:33.995 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] Okay, but the question
is, where do we even start?

00:07:34.079 --> 00:07:36.164 position:50% align:center
There are so many
carriages today.

00:07:36.247 --> 00:07:37.415 position:50% align:center
I wonder what's happening.

00:07:37.499 --> 00:07:40.043 position:50% align:center
I heard they're revealing
something amazing.

00:07:40.126 --> 00:07:42.087 position:50% align:center
I mean, at the castle ball,
of course.

00:07:43.338 --> 00:07:45.965 position:50% align:center
They say the emperor
captured a mermaid

00:07:46.049 --> 00:07:48.468 position:50% align:center
and now he plans to
show it to the world!

00:07:48.551 --> 00:07:51.638 position:50% align:center
It sings, "Darling! Darling!"
Romantic, right?

00:07:51.721 --> 00:07:53.890 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:07:54.099 --> 00:07:56.393 position:50% align:center
[alarms]

00:07:56.476 --> 00:07:57.686 position:50% align:center
[SHIIZAKI] We're seeing
scattered battles

00:07:57.769 --> 00:07:59.229 position:50% align:center
around the base!

00:07:59.312 --> 00:08:02.565 position:50% align:center
[MIKIMOTO] DEM Wizards and
Bandersnatch are now confirmed!

00:08:02.649 --> 00:08:03.525 position:50% align:center
The Commander?

00:08:03.608 --> 00:08:05.026 position:50% align:center
There's no way to reach her!

00:08:05.110 --> 00:08:07.862 position:50% align:center
Oh god, help us!
Misty help us!

00:08:07.946 --> 00:08:11.491 position:50% align:center
[MARIA] Relax. Breathe deep.
In times like these,

00:08:11.574 --> 00:08:13.868 position:50% align:center
losing your cool can be
even more dangerous

00:08:13.952 --> 00:08:17.080 position:50% align:center
than anything the enemy
can attempt to trip you up.

00:08:17.163 --> 00:08:18.665 position:50% align:center
[MARIA]
Don't worry.

00:08:18.748 --> 00:08:22.544 position:50% align:center
Rest assured, I know the crew's
capabilities better than anyone.

00:08:22.627 --> 00:08:24.295 position:50% align:center
Well, now you've done it.

00:08:24.379 --> 00:08:26.840 position:50% align:center
You've officially
stolen my thunder.

00:08:26.923 --> 00:08:29.426 position:50% align:center
Like MARIA said,
let's remain calm.

00:08:29.509 --> 00:08:31.302 position:50% align:center
Has there been any
word from base?

00:08:31.386 --> 00:08:33.847 position:50% align:center
We have, and Woodman is safe.

00:08:33.930 --> 00:08:36.391 position:50% align:center
He's strongly urging us
to take Fraxinus.

00:08:36.474 --> 00:08:39.227 position:50% align:center
He also says we should
head to Zodiac, now.

00:08:39.310 --> 00:08:41.312 position:50% align:center
If that's what he
thinks we should do,

00:08:41.396 --> 00:08:44.733 position:50% align:center
then let us protect it until
all the others have returned.

00:08:45.817 --> 00:08:47.068 position:50% align:center
[MINOWA]
Damage to our hull!

00:08:47.152 --> 00:08:49.821 position:50% align:center
It appears enemies have
breached the hangar!

00:08:49.904 --> 00:08:54.367 position:50% align:center
MARIA, set Territory to
50 and activate jamming.

00:08:54.451 --> 00:08:57.120 position:50% align:center
[MARIA] Acknowledged.
Deploying Territory.

00:09:00.540 --> 00:09:02.542 position:50% align:center
[KANNAZUKI] Our Territory
has neutralized the enemy,

00:09:02.625 --> 00:09:04.044 position:50% align:center
as it's deadly to them.

00:09:04.127 --> 00:09:06.838 position:50% align:center
To any machine using
generative magic,

00:09:06.921 --> 00:09:08.340 position:50% align:center
it gets the job done.

00:09:08.423 --> 00:09:09.841 position:50% align:center
Nice, Vice Commander!

00:09:09.924 --> 00:09:13.053 position:50% align:center
Although, at the end of
the day, it's just Territory.

00:09:13.136 --> 00:09:15.388 position:50% align:center
It does nothing to stop
humans and bullets.

00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:17.974 position:50% align:center
[MALE WIZARD A]
Hands up!

00:09:18.058 --> 00:09:19.559 position:50% align:center
[MALE WIZARD B]
Don't move or we'll shoot!

00:09:22.395 --> 00:09:24.439 position:50% align:center
[MALE WIZARD C]
So, this is Fraxinus, is it?

00:09:24.522 --> 00:09:25.607 position:50% align:center
[MALE WIZARD B]
Westcott will be pleased.

00:09:25.690 --> 00:09:26.649 position:50% align:center
No doubt about that.

00:09:26.733 --> 00:09:30.153 position:50% align:center
--[GROWLING]
--[MALE WIZARDS gasp]

00:09:33.698 --> 00:09:35.241 position:50% align:center
[MALE WIZARDS gasp]

00:09:37.118 --> 00:09:42.165 position:50% align:center
--[GROWLING]
--[MALE WIZARDS yell]

00:09:45.669 --> 00:09:48.046 position:50% align:center
Our MARIA really
enjoys her projections!

00:09:48.129 --> 00:09:50.006 position:50% align:center
[MALE WIZARD A groans]

00:09:50.090 --> 00:09:53.718 position:50% align:center
[NAKATSUGAWA yells]

00:09:55.303 --> 00:09:58.139 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:09:58.223 --> 00:10:04.020 position:50% align:center
[NAKATSUGAWA]
No. No. Misty, no! Misty!

00:10:04.104 --> 00:10:07.607 position:50% align:center
How dare you lay a
finger on my Misty!

00:10:09.234 --> 00:10:11.403 position:50% align:center
[MALE WIZARD B groans]

00:10:11.486 --> 00:10:15.740 position:50% align:center
[MALE WIZARD C gasps, screams]

00:10:17.534 --> 00:10:22.747 position:50% align:center
[MALE WIZARD C groans]

00:10:22.831 --> 00:10:24.249 position:50% align:center
[MARIA]
Good work, everyone.

00:10:24.332 --> 00:10:27.335 position:50% align:center
Now addressing:
Nakatsugawa, Shiizaki.

00:10:27.419 --> 00:10:28.586 position:50% align:center
Yes, Maria?

00:10:28.670 --> 00:10:29.963 position:50% align:center
[MARIA]
You've demonstrated the value

00:10:30.046 --> 00:10:31.965 position:50% align:center
of figures and straw dolls.

00:10:32.048 --> 00:10:34.926 position:50% align:center
I'm granting permission to
bring them onto the bridge.

00:10:36.803 --> 00:10:40.390 position:50% align:center
[NAKATSUGAWA]
Misty!

00:10:49.941 --> 00:10:54.112 position:50% align:center
Wow. It's the storyboard for
every fairytale castle, ever.

00:10:54.195 --> 00:10:56.531 position:50% align:center
Lots of people come
through here, for sure.

00:10:56.614 --> 00:10:58.908 position:50% align:center
We might manage to
learn something.

00:10:58.992 --> 00:11:00.744 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
C'mon, would you just let us in?

00:11:00.827 --> 00:11:02.245 position:50% align:center
Shido, you see?

00:11:02.328 --> 00:11:03.246 position:50% align:center
[NIA, SHIDO gasp]

00:11:03.329 --> 00:11:04.122 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Meanie!

00:11:04.205 --> 00:11:05.498 position:50% align:center
[YUZURU]
Stubborn moose.

00:11:05.582 --> 00:11:07.876 position:50% align:center
Kotori! Kaguya! Yuzuru!

00:11:07.959 --> 00:11:09.336 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:11:09.419 --> 00:11:12.130 position:50% align:center
Shido! So, you're all right!

00:11:12.213 --> 00:11:14.507 position:50% align:center
Except for this pig thing,
what's happening?

00:11:14.591 --> 00:11:16.217 position:50% align:center
You looked in a mirror yet?

00:11:16.301 --> 00:11:19.137 position:50% align:center
Excuse me, but is
there a problem here?

00:11:19.220 --> 00:11:21.097 position:50% align:center
We came because we wanted
to see the mermaid

00:11:21.181 --> 00:11:22.724 position:50% align:center
everyone's talking about.

00:11:22.807 --> 00:11:24.684 position:50% align:center
And it cries, "Darling!"

00:11:24.768 --> 00:11:26.644 position:50% align:center
At least that's what
we've been hearing.

00:11:26.728 --> 00:11:28.396 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Hm. Very interesting.

00:11:28.480 --> 00:11:31.316 position:50% align:center
But now, this guard is
being a straight-up doofus!

00:11:31.399 --> 00:11:32.567 position:50% align:center
Pissed off.

00:11:32.650 --> 00:11:34.611 position:50% align:center
He won't let us through
and I hate it very much.

00:11:34.694 --> 00:11:35.945 position:50% align:center
What'd you expect?

00:11:36.029 --> 00:11:38.156 position:50% align:center
You're not about to get
past me dressed like that!

00:11:38.239 --> 00:11:39.616 position:50% align:center
You all look messed up!

00:11:39.699 --> 00:11:42.619 position:50% align:center
[ALL sigh, gasp]

00:11:46.998 --> 00:11:50.001 position:50% align:center
[NATSUMI] Greetings, friends.
It's good to see you.

00:11:50.085 --> 00:11:51.503 position:50% align:center
Natsumi?

00:11:56.925 --> 00:12:00.720 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:12:02.347 --> 00:12:05.642 position:50% align:center
Please sir, these people
are my close attendants.

00:12:05.725 --> 00:12:07.811 position:50% align:center
May they enter through
the gates with me?

00:12:07.894 --> 00:12:11.272 position:50% align:center
Well, uh. It's just... I mean...

00:12:11.356 --> 00:12:14.526 position:50% align:center
Thanks. We're good?

00:12:14.609 --> 00:12:17.153 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Of course. Go on ahead.

00:12:17.237 --> 00:12:18.988 position:50% align:center
[bells chime]

00:12:19.072 --> 00:12:20.281 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:12:21.741 --> 00:12:24.119 position:50% align:center
[MALE GUARDS gasp]

00:12:28.373 --> 00:12:29.165 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:12:29.249 --> 00:12:31.418 position:50% align:center
Why you...! You little...!

00:12:31.501 --> 00:12:33.545 position:50% align:center
You little fake!

00:12:33.628 --> 00:12:37.757 position:50% align:center
[ALL scream]

00:12:37.841 --> 00:12:39.426 position:50% align:center
[ALL pant]

00:12:39.509 --> 00:12:42.554 position:50% align:center
[NIA] So, we've established
Natsumi is Cinderella.

00:12:42.637 --> 00:12:44.264 position:50% align:center
[NATSUMI]
No big shock there.

00:12:44.347 --> 00:12:47.976 position:50% align:center
Look! At this rate, I think
using force is the only option!

00:12:48.059 --> 00:12:49.394 position:50% align:center
Fired up.

00:12:49.477 --> 00:12:51.855 position:50% align:center
She's right, with our numbers,
we don't need Angels.

00:12:51.938 --> 00:12:55.525 position:50% align:center
Hold on. Let's take our time
and be smart about this.

00:13:06.536 --> 00:13:09.539 position:50% align:center
It's a good plan, Kotori.
Well done.

00:13:09.622 --> 00:13:11.833 position:50% align:center
If you let the candle die,
we'll change back.

00:13:11.916 --> 00:13:13.918 position:50% align:center
So just be very careful.

00:13:14.002 --> 00:13:17.213 position:50% align:center
[SHIORI grunts] 'Kay, but why do
I have to wear a dress, too?

00:13:17.297 --> 00:13:18.840 position:50% align:center
You're about to learn
how much easier it is

00:13:18.923 --> 00:13:21.843 position:50% align:center
to slide your way into a ball
when you're wearing a dress.

00:13:21.926 --> 00:13:25.472 position:50% align:center
[music plays]

00:13:25.555 --> 00:13:27.724 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:13:31.186 --> 00:13:33.563 position:50% align:center
This is an obscene
level of fanciness.

00:13:33.646 --> 00:13:35.857 position:50% align:center
Guess that's
Cinderella's ball for you.

00:13:35.940 --> 00:13:37.901 position:50% align:center
I don't see a mermaid, do you?

00:13:37.984 --> 00:13:40.362 position:50% align:center
There's not a single
fin in sight here.

00:13:40.445 --> 00:13:43.698 position:50% align:center
Honored guests, please turn
your attention to the stage!

00:13:43.782 --> 00:13:47.577 position:50% align:center
For the time has now come to
behold the song of the mermaid!

00:13:53.083 --> 00:13:54.125 position:50% align:center
[ALL]
Miku!

00:13:54.209 --> 00:13:56.711 position:50% align:center
[MIKU gasps]
Darling! Everyone!

00:13:56.795 --> 00:13:59.339 position:50% align:center
Just look at the lovely
dresses you're wearing!

00:13:59.422 --> 00:14:01.383 position:50% align:center
Oh, and Darling's
in Shiori-mode!

00:14:01.466 --> 00:14:03.927 position:50% align:center
Well, what're we waiting for?
Give me the details!

00:14:04.010 --> 00:14:06.304 position:50% align:center
Did anyone even think
to record it for me?

00:14:06.388 --> 00:14:08.223 position:50% align:center
[SHIORI]
Hey! Listen, calm down!

00:14:08.306 --> 00:14:11.059 position:50% align:center
By the way, how did you end up
here in the first place?

00:14:11.142 --> 00:14:13.770 position:50% align:center
I don't know, suddenly,
I was just there in the water.

00:14:13.853 --> 00:14:16.106 position:50% align:center
Before I knew it,
there was an evil witch.

00:14:16.189 --> 00:14:17.982 position:50% align:center
Then she promised she would
make me human again

00:14:18.066 --> 00:14:19.651 position:50% align:center
in exchange for my voice.

00:14:19.734 --> 00:14:22.404 position:50% align:center
So, guess we've got
ourselves a Little Mermaid.

00:14:22.487 --> 00:14:24.739 position:50% align:center
And yet you're still
in mermaid form.

00:14:24.823 --> 00:14:26.282 position:50% align:center
[MIKU]
That's right.

00:14:26.366 --> 00:14:28.910 position:50% align:center
I would never let anyone take my
voice, so I just smacked her

00:14:28.993 --> 00:14:30.787 position:50% align:center
around with my tail
and took off instead!

00:14:30.870 --> 00:14:32.288 position:50% align:center
Which was the best!

00:14:32.372 --> 00:14:34.165 position:50% align:center
Well, that is until
some fishermen

00:14:34.249 --> 00:14:35.917 position:50% align:center
caught me on the beach.

00:14:36.001 --> 00:14:36.918 position:50% align:center
[ORIGAMI]
What's the commotion?

00:14:37.002 --> 00:14:38.962 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:14:43.508 --> 00:14:44.801 position:50% align:center
It's our emperor!

00:14:44.884 --> 00:14:45.635 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:14:45.719 --> 00:14:46.928 position:50% align:center
Oh, my!

00:14:47.012 --> 00:14:48.221 position:50% align:center
[ORIGAMI]
Hm.

00:14:49.514 --> 00:14:51.433 position:50% align:center
Oh! So, that's the rumored...

00:14:51.516 --> 00:14:54.060 position:50% align:center
Look at her amazing outfit!
I'm obsessed!

00:14:54.144 --> 00:14:57.647 position:50% align:center
Seriously! It's like a
veil of mist! Gorgeous!

00:15:00.525 --> 00:15:04.696 position:50% align:center
Shido, everyone.
I'm glad you're okay.

00:15:04.779 --> 00:15:09.325 position:50% align:center
Yeah, we're good.
How about you? You okay?

00:15:09.409 --> 00:15:11.327 position:50% align:center
Not sure I get
why you're asking.

00:15:11.411 --> 00:15:15.457 position:50% align:center
Let's see. How to put this?
You didn't get mugged, did you?

00:15:15.540 --> 00:15:18.418 position:50% align:center
Honestly? What do you think
you're wearing right now?

00:15:18.501 --> 00:15:19.586 position:50% align:center
You're totally naked!

00:15:19.669 --> 00:15:21.421 position:50% align:center
[AlL gasp]

00:15:21.504 --> 00:15:23.006 position:50% align:center
I can't believe she did that!

00:15:23.089 --> 00:15:26.009 position:50% align:center
She just insulted the
emperor's clothes! How dare!

00:15:26.092 --> 00:15:28.970 position:50% align:center
Have a look. I got it
from wandering tailors.

00:15:29.054 --> 00:15:32.265 position:50% align:center
Those who are without love
for Shido can't see it.

00:15:32.349 --> 00:15:34.809 position:50% align:center
So, considering you
can't see it, Tohka.

00:15:34.893 --> 00:15:38.104 position:50% align:center
Uh, no! Wait, hold on!
You know...

00:15:38.188 --> 00:15:41.399 position:50% align:center
Now I can see, they're splendid
skin-like clothes, aren't they?

00:15:41.483 --> 00:15:43.693 position:50% align:center
No need to go that far, Tohka.

00:15:43.777 --> 00:15:46.154 position:50% align:center
This is the tale of The
Emperor's New Clothes.

00:15:46.237 --> 00:15:48.365 position:50% align:center
The Emperor's New Clothes?

00:15:51.493 --> 00:15:53.161 position:50% align:center
[ORIGAMI]
I swear I had no idea.

00:15:53.244 --> 00:15:55.830 position:50% align:center
Surely you must've thought
it was strange, though?

00:15:55.914 --> 00:15:57.874 position:50% align:center
When they said you can't
see it without love,

00:15:57.957 --> 00:15:59.084 position:50% align:center
I caught a glimpse,

00:15:59.167 --> 00:16:02.170 position:50% align:center
but then I chalked it
up to my own issues.

00:16:02.253 --> 00:16:03.713 position:50% align:center
Huh. Interesting.

00:16:03.797 --> 00:16:05.507 position:50% align:center
But this is a good thing.

00:16:05.590 --> 00:16:07.550 position:50% align:center
'Cause we're all
back together again.

00:16:07.634 --> 00:16:10.136 position:50% align:center
Yeah. And Origami's emperor,

00:16:10.220 --> 00:16:12.263 position:50% align:center
so she'll use her
power to help us.

00:16:12.347 --> 00:16:15.684 position:50% align:center
She can search the lands far
and wide for a superhero.

00:16:15.767 --> 00:16:17.435 position:50% align:center
A "Superhero"?

00:16:17.519 --> 00:16:19.020 position:50% align:center
Yup!

00:16:19.104 --> 00:16:20.814 position:50% align:center
You never know, there might be
somebody powerful around here

00:16:20.897 --> 00:16:22.732 position:50% align:center
who can help return
us to our world.

00:16:22.816 --> 00:16:25.568 position:50% align:center
I mean, it's at least worth
taking a look, don't you think?

00:16:25.652 --> 00:16:27.821 position:50% align:center
That's true. I'm powerful.

00:16:27.904 --> 00:16:30.657 position:50% align:center
I can issue a search
of the entire land.

00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:33.576 position:50% align:center
It's possible that we could
find an item or something.

00:16:33.660 --> 00:16:35.745 position:50% align:center
Oh, good! It sounds like
we'll be getting back

00:16:35.829 --> 00:16:37.664 position:50% align:center
to our world in
no time, everyone!

00:16:37.747 --> 00:16:39.249 position:50% align:center
Let's get started right away!

00:16:39.332 --> 00:16:40.625 position:50% align:center
[WOLF growls]

00:16:40.709 --> 00:16:41.543 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]
Huh?

00:16:41.626 --> 00:16:43.920 position:50% align:center
[WOLF grunts, chuckles]

00:16:44.004 --> 00:16:46.506 position:50% align:center
[ALL scream]

00:16:46.589 --> 00:16:48.550 position:50% align:center
[SHIORI]
Crap! The wolf's back!

00:16:50.719 --> 00:16:52.554 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:16:52.637 --> 00:16:54.681 position:50% align:center
[RED, BLUE OGRE grunt]

00:16:54.764 --> 00:16:55.890 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:16:55.974 --> 00:16:59.060 position:50% align:center
It can't be!
Ogres from Onigashima?

00:16:59.144 --> 00:17:00.729 position:50% align:center
Seemed like you
weren't coming,

00:17:00.812 --> 00:17:03.106 position:50% align:center
so we came here to find you!

00:17:04.607 --> 00:17:06.317 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
What the hell?

00:17:06.401 --> 00:17:08.278 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah, sorry, that's mine.

00:17:08.361 --> 00:17:10.030 position:50% align:center
There's this monster
guy in Silver Bullet

00:17:10.113 --> 00:17:13.116 position:50% align:center
that revives in Part Two, gets a
lot more powerful in Part Three,

00:17:13.199 --> 00:17:16.077 position:50% align:center
and finally, he seeks
revenge on Fatima.

00:17:16.161 --> 00:17:18.204 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO] Curse those
damn recurring villains.

00:17:18.288 --> 00:17:21.791 position:50% align:center
[MONSTERS growl]

00:17:23.043 --> 00:17:23.960 position:50% align:center
So be it!

00:17:24.044 --> 00:17:25.295 position:50% align:center
Wait a minute!

00:17:25.378 --> 00:17:27.505 position:50% align:center
We can't even use our
Spirit power here, can we?

00:17:27.589 --> 00:17:28.840 position:50% align:center
There's no way we can win!

00:17:28.923 --> 00:17:31.217 position:50% align:center
Well, then, what do
you think we should do?

00:17:31.301 --> 00:17:33.386 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:33.470 --> 00:17:35.221 position:50% align:center
[MUKURO] Are the Spirits
you claim to "save"

00:17:35.305 --> 00:17:36.681 position:50% align:center
not exposed to greater peril?

00:17:36.765 --> 00:17:39.976 position:50% align:center
Sealing my powers might
worsen the circumstances.

00:17:40.060 --> 00:17:41.478 position:50% align:center
Well, Shido?

00:17:41.561 --> 00:17:44.564 position:50% align:center
Your intentions are noble,
but I tire of this hypocrisy.

00:17:46.358 --> 00:17:47.567 position:50% align:center
Run, you guys!

00:17:47.650 --> 00:17:49.152 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:17:49.235 --> 00:17:51.988 position:50% align:center
[growls]

00:17:52.072 --> 00:17:53.615 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:17:53.698 --> 00:17:55.992 position:50% align:center
[WOLF howls]

00:18:00.413 --> 00:18:02.415 position:50% align:center
Who the hell do
you think you are?

00:18:02.499 --> 00:18:05.126 position:50% align:center
Just a neighborhood
high schooler.

00:18:06.628 --> 00:18:07.837 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:18:11.466 --> 00:18:14.886 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp, chatter]

00:18:14.969 --> 00:18:16.638 position:50% align:center
Oh! That's it!

00:18:16.721 --> 00:18:18.682 position:50% align:center
He's the Shido from
that manga we drew!

00:18:18.765 --> 00:18:20.183 position:50% align:center
That makes sense.

00:18:20.266 --> 00:18:23.436 position:50% align:center
Since this world is a big mashup
of all different stories!

00:18:23.520 --> 00:18:25.522 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI] It's not that
unusual for the "Shido"

00:18:25.605 --> 00:18:27.774 position:50% align:center
from our manga to be here.

00:18:27.857 --> 00:18:29.984 position:50% align:center
[NIA] And what's more,
he's all at once exactly

00:18:30.068 --> 00:18:32.946 position:50% align:center
like the Shido Itsuka
we know, but also not!

00:18:33.029 --> 00:18:34.823 position:50% align:center
He's a total manga hero!

00:18:34.906 --> 00:18:38.868 position:50% align:center
'Cause he's both super
cool and super strong!

00:18:38.952 --> 00:18:40.787 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Hey, you okay, other me?

00:18:40.870 --> 00:18:43.456 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I'm good.
Thank you, other me.

00:18:43.540 --> 00:18:46.292 position:50% align:center
Ha, ha! You know who
we sound like?

00:18:46.376 --> 00:18:48.503 position:50% align:center
Kurumi, all the way.

00:18:48.586 --> 00:18:50.797 position:50% align:center
This can't be good news.

00:18:50.880 --> 00:18:52.674 position:50% align:center
If you're all here,
I'm gonna go ahead and assume

00:18:52.757 --> 00:18:54.426 position:50% align:center
that Westcott's
involved somehow.

00:18:54.509 --> 00:18:57.137 position:50% align:center
Thank you, that saves us
the trouble of explaining.

00:18:57.220 --> 00:18:59.055 position:50% align:center
Can we return to
our world somehow?

00:18:59.139 --> 00:19:02.809 position:50% align:center
We really do need to get back
there as soon as possible.

00:19:02.892 --> 00:19:05.645 position:50% align:center
Stop worrying.
Leave it all to me.

00:19:06.771 --> 00:19:09.941 position:50% align:center
A Demon King is responsible
for creating this world.

00:19:10.025 --> 00:19:14.195 position:50% align:center
So we know that means it can
be broken apart by an Angel.

00:19:14.279 --> 00:19:16.156 position:50% align:center
Though I may be fiction,

00:19:16.239 --> 00:19:21.036 position:50% align:center
while I exist in this world, my
Angel's a hundred percent real.

00:19:21.119 --> 00:19:23.663 position:50% align:center
[shouts]

00:19:26.207 --> 00:19:28.251 position:50% align:center
We should be able to
get back through here!

00:19:28.335 --> 00:19:29.294 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:19:29.377 --> 00:19:31.212 position:50% align:center
Thank you so much, Shido!

00:19:39.596 --> 00:19:40.930 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA grunts]

00:19:42.807 --> 00:19:44.392 position:50% align:center
Um. Hey, me?

00:19:44.476 --> 00:19:47.270 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Hm? Hey, what's up, me?

00:19:47.354 --> 00:19:48.855 position:50% align:center
Well, it's just that...

00:19:48.938 --> 00:19:53.526 position:50% align:center
I'm supposed to help this
Spirit named Mukuro, but now...

00:19:53.610 --> 00:19:56.571 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO] Hm. You're having
some doubts. You're thinking,

00:19:56.654 --> 00:19:58.531 position:50% align:center
"maybe if I hadn't sealed
the Spirits' powers,

00:19:58.615 --> 00:20:00.658 position:50% align:center
they wouldn't be in danger.
Or at least they wouldn't have

00:20:00.742 --> 00:20:03.328 position:50% align:center
to be facing the kind
of trials they are now."

00:20:03.411 --> 00:20:05.413 position:50% align:center
You're wondering if maybe
you made the wrong choice

00:20:05.497 --> 00:20:07.540 position:50% align:center
in all this.

00:20:07.624 --> 00:20:11.002 position:50% align:center
I get it, I mean,
because you're me.

00:20:11.086 --> 00:20:14.464 position:50% align:center
But no matter what,
I'd help that Spirit.

00:20:14.547 --> 00:20:15.674 position:50% align:center
I would try.

00:20:15.757 --> 00:20:18.927 position:50% align:center
I know, but she just
wants to be left alone.

00:20:19.010 --> 00:20:20.970 position:50% align:center
Yes, that's true,

00:20:21.054 --> 00:20:23.473 position:50% align:center
but doesn't it seem
kinda strange to you?

00:20:23.556 --> 00:20:27.477 position:50% align:center
She locked her whole heart away
just so she wouldn't be sad?

00:20:27.560 --> 00:20:29.396 position:50% align:center
She must've experienced
a lot of sadness

00:20:29.479 --> 00:20:32.774 position:50% align:center
already to resort to something
as extreme as that.

00:20:32.857 --> 00:20:33.775 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO gasps]

00:20:33.858 --> 00:20:35.110 position:50% align:center
Think about it.

00:20:35.193 --> 00:20:38.738 position:50% align:center
Her words actually sound
like a cry for help to me.

00:20:38.822 --> 00:20:42.325 position:50% align:center
For starters, what is
it I want for her?

00:20:42.409 --> 00:20:46.496 position:50% align:center
You're right.
What does she need?

00:20:46.579 --> 00:20:49.666 position:50% align:center
Now I see. I've got it.

00:20:49.749 --> 00:20:50.959 position:50% align:center
Thank you.

00:20:51.042 --> 00:20:54.838 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO chuckles]
Well, high schooler, good luck.

00:20:54.921 --> 00:20:57.966 position:50% align:center
Same to you,
random neighborhood guy!

00:21:01.052 --> 00:21:02.262 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:21:03.471 --> 00:21:05.015 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI]
Took ya long enough, Shido.

00:21:05.098 --> 00:21:06.433 position:50% align:center
[SHIDO]
Hm?

00:21:06.516 --> 00:21:07.892 position:50% align:center
What now?

00:21:07.976 --> 00:21:10.687 position:50% align:center
Were you able to talk it all
out with the other Shido?

00:21:10.770 --> 00:21:13.189 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:21:13.273 --> 00:21:16.776 position:50% align:center
Yeah. A bit. I'm good.

00:21:16.860 --> 00:21:19.738 position:50% align:center
Now, let's do this!
Let's save Mukuro!

00:21:22.532 --> 00:21:24.617 position:50% align:center
Huh? They're back!

00:21:24.701 --> 00:21:28.204 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]

00:21:28.288 --> 00:21:29.581 position:50% align:center
[KOTORI grunts]

00:21:29.664 --> 00:21:32.167 position:50% align:center
Right, now let's get to
Mukuro as quickly as we can.

00:21:32.250 --> 00:21:36.087 position:50% align:center
Prepare to launch!
Realizers in parallel drive!

00:21:36.171 --> 00:21:41.634 position:50% align:center
Deploy Territory in avoid mode!
Fraxinus Excelsior, lift off!

00:22:05.533 --> 00:22:10.538 position:50% align:center line:10%
♪

00:23:35.665 --> 00:23:37.625 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
Fraxinus gets a new life, 

00:23:37.709 --> 00:23:41.171 position:50% align:center
but blocking their way
is Ellen, in Goetia.

00:23:41.254 --> 00:23:43.340 position:50% align:center
How will this fated
showdown end?

00:23:43.423 --> 00:23:45.008 position:50% align:center
Only time will tell.

00:23:45.091 --> 00:23:47.260 position:50% align:center
Next time: "An Opened Heart".

00:23:47.344 --> 00:23:49.929 position:50% align:center
Shido and Mukuro's
destiny awaits!